---
layout: base
---
%body.commons
  #layout.layout-wide
    / Header Section
    %header.index_static
      .nav_logo.animated.fadeIn
        .container
          .row
            %nav.col-md-12
              %ul#menu.sf-menu
                %li 
                  %a{:href => "#join"} Join Commons
                %li
                  %a{:href => "#colleagues"} Participants
                %li 
                  %a{:href => "#interests"} Interests
                %li
                  %a{:href => "briefings.html"} Events & Briefings
                %li
                  %a{:href => "quotes.html"} Participant Quotes
      %section.content_info
        .bg_parallax.image_06_parallax
          %section.opacy_bg_05.paddings
            / Info Head Static
            .container
              .row
                .col-md-12
                  .logo.wow.fadeIn.delay
                    %a{:href => "index.html", :title => "Back to Home"}
                      %img.logo_img{:alt => "Logo", :src => "img/openshift_logo_horizontal_wht.svg", :style => "margin-bottom: 30px"}/
                  %h1.animated.fadeInDown.delay
                    OpenShift Commons
                  %p.animated.fadeInUp.delay
                    Where partners, customers, and contributors come together to collaborate and work together using OpenShift. 
    / Info title
    %section.content_info#join
      #try.info_title.wow.fadeInDown
        %i.fa.fa-users.right
        .vertical_line
          .circle_bottom
        .info_vertical.animated
          %h1
            OpenShift
            %span Commons
        .padding_bottom
          .container.wow.fadeInUp.animated
            .row
              .col-xs-12.col-sm-12.col-md-6.col-lg-6.lead
                %p.text-left Commons builds connections and collaboration across OpenShift communities, projects and stakeholders. In doing so we'll enable the success of customers, users, partners, and contributors as we deepen our knowledge and experiences together.

                %br
                %p.text-left Our goals go beyond code contributions. Commons is a place for companies using OpenShift to accelerate its success and adoption. To do this we'll act as resources for each other, share best practices and provide a forum for peer-to-peer communication.
              %h2 Join Now
              / Form
              = partial ('main_signup.html.haml')
              / End Form
    / End Info title
    / End content info - Grey Section
    %section.content_info#colleagues
      / Info Resalt
      .info_resalt.borders
        .info_vertical
          %h1
            Commons
            %span Participants
        .container
          / Items Works filters
          .portfolioContainer
            / Item Work
            - File.open("img/participants.txt").readlines.each do |line|
              - img = line.split(',').map(&:chomp)
              .col-sm-2.col-md-2.col-lg-2.col-xs-4.desing
                .item-work
                  %a{:href => "#{img[1]}", :alt => " #{img[0]}", :title => " #{img[0]}"}
                    .logo
                      .hover
                        %img{:alt => "Image", :src => "img/#{img[2]}"}/
                  .info
                    %a{:href => "#{img[0]}"} #{img[0]}
              / End Item Work
          / End Items Works filters
      / End Info Resalt
    / End content info - Grey Section
    / Info title
    %section.content_info#interests
      .row.info_title
        .vertical_line
          .circle_bottom
        .info_vertical
          %h1
            Find Your
            %span Commonality
          %p.text-left OpenShift is an inclusive, open and inviting community filled with passionate people. Chances are, there is a local OpenShift event near you already in the works, check out our Events calendar or connect with the OpenShift Accelerators nearest you and organize your own local event.
          .row
            .paddings
              .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.col-md-6.col-lg-6.wow.fadeInLeft
                %h2 
                  %a{:href => "sig/Operations.html", :title => "Operations"} OpenShift Ops
                  %p Discuss, develop and disseminate best practices for administrating, managing and operating OpenShift
              .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.col-md-6.col-lg-6.wow.fadeInRight
                %h2 
                  %a{:href => "sig/Openshift3.html", :title => "OpenShift 3"} OpenShift 3
                  %p OpenShift V3 Migration Upgrade Roadmap Special Interest Group
              -# .col-xs-12.col-sm-4.col-md-4.col-lg-4.wow.fadeInRight
              -#   %h2 
              -#     %a{:href => "sig/Ecosystem.html", :title => "Ecosystem"} Ecosystem
              -#     %p Collaboration in practice
        .vertical_line
        %i.fa.fa-comments-o.right
      / End Info title
      / Info title
    %section.content_info
      / Info Resalt
      .info_resalt.borders
        .container
          .row
            .col-md-12.simple-title
              %h2
                Participant 
                %span Quotes
            / carousel-team-members
            #carousel-team-members.col-md-12
              - File.open("img/quotes.txt").readlines.each do |line|
                - img = line.split(',').map(&:chomp)
                / Item Team
                .item-team
                  .logo
                    %img{:alt => "Image", :src => "img/#{img[2]}"}
                  %h4
                    %a{:href => "#{img[4]}", :alt => " #{img[0]}", :title => " #{img[0]}"} #{img[0]}
                  %p #{img[3]}
                / End Item Team
            / End carousel-team-members
      / End Info Resalt
    %section.content_info.paddings
      .row.info_title.wow.fadeInUp
        .info_vertical
          %h1
            Become a part of something
            %span bigger
          %p OpenShift Commons open to OpenShift users (individuals), enterprises, non-profits, educational institutions, partners, service providers, hosting providers  and related open source technology projects that are either utilized under the hood or to extend the platform with services and additional functionality.
          %br
          %ul
            %li.text-left If you (or your organization)  are an OpenShift Online or an OpenShift Enterprise  customer or you have deploy OpenShift Origin on premise or on a public cloud, this is the forum for you to connect with your peers.

            %li.text-left If you have extended OpenShift with your services or contributed to the OpenShift Origin project and want to connect with your peers and those users of your services on OpenShift, this is the forum for you.

            %li.text-left If you simply want to stay up-to-date on the roadmap and best practices for using, deploying and operating OpenShift, the OpenShift Commons is the right place for you.

          %h2
            %a{:href => "#join"} Ready to Join?
        %i.fa.fa-compass.left            
    / End Info title
    / End content info - Grey Section
    /footer              